I can think of two things that would help the warrior class without unbalancing them.  Improve their taunt so that it generates a certain percent more hate than other classes' taunts (let's say 25-35%), and give them all a stunning attack that doesn't need a sheild.  Nothing big...something like the large race's "slam" ability, but exclusive to warriors and not limited to large races.  Stunning abilities are increasingly important as levels go up...which is why most LDON groups want paladins and shadowknights.  Most warriors drop sheild use once they get dual wield, in favor of the higher damage output they can do with two weapons.

I think those two things would improve their ability to keep aggro as the MT without making them too powerful.  After all, they get all those hit points so they can take more damage than anyone else.  What's the point if they can't hold the mob's attention?

People make warriors so that they can be in the front line, not to solo or chase the mobs around trying to regain aggro.  All those nice hit points go to waste, and I'm beginning to understand why I see so many warriors between level 50-65 using two handed blunt (that staff of thunder or whatever from LDON is very popular now).  If using fast weapons for aggro isn't doing you any good, you might as well go for the higher damaging weapons, right?

